  "chapter": {
    "number": 8,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Assyrian Invasion Prophesied"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Then the LORD said to me, “Take a large scroll and write on it with an ordinary",
          {
            "noteId": 2534
          },
          "stylus: Maher-shalal-hash-baz.",
          {
            "noteId": 2535
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "And I will appoint for Myself trustworthy witnesses—Uriah the priest and Zechariah son of Jeberekiah.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "And I had relations with the prophetess, and she conceived and gave birth to a son. The LORD said to me, “Name him Maher-shalal-hash-baz."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "For before the boy knows how to cry ‘Father’ or ‘Mother,’ the wealth of Damascus and the plunder of Samaria will be carried off by the king of Assyria.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "And the LORD spoke to me further:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Because this people has rejected",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the gently flowing waters of Shiloah",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and rejoiced in Rezin",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the son of Remaliah,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "the Lord will surely bring against them",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the mighty floodwaters of the Euphrates",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2536
          },
          {
            "text": "—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the king of Assyria and all his pomp.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "It will overflow its channels",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and overrun its banks.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It will pour into Judah,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "swirling and sweeping over it,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "reaching up to the neck;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "its spreading streams will cover",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your entire land, O Immanuel!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2537
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Huddle together,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2538
          },
          {
            "text": "O peoples, and be shattered;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "pay attention, all you distant lands;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "prepare for battle, and be shattered;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "prepare for battle, and be shattered!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Devise a plan, but it will be thwarted;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "state a proposal, but it will not happen.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For God is with us.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2539
          },
          {
            "text": "”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Call to Fear God"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "For this is what the LORD has spoken to me with a strong hand, instructing me not to walk in the way of this people:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Do not call conspiracy",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "everything these people regard as conspiracy.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Do not fear what they fear;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2540
          },
          {
            "text": "do not live in dread.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2541
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD of Hosts is the One",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you shall regard as holy.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Only He should be feared;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "only He should be dreaded.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And He will be a sanctuary—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but to both houses of Israel",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a stone of stumbling and a rock of offense,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2542
          },
          {
            "text": "to the dwellers of Jerusalem",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a trap and a snare.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Many will stumble over these;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will fall and be broken;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they will be ensnared and captured.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bind up the testimony",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and seal the law among my disciples.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will wait for the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who is hiding His face from the house of Jacob.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will put my trust in Him.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2543
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          "Here am I, and the children the LORD has given me",
          {
            "noteId": 2544
          },
          "as signs and symbols in Israel from the LORD of Hosts, who dwells on Mount Zion."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Darkness and Light"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          "When men tell you to consult the spirits of the dead and the spiritists who whisper and mutter, shouldn’t a people consult their God instead? Why consult the dead on behalf of the living?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          "To the law and to the testimony! If they do not speak according to this word, they have no light of dawn."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          "They will roam the land, dejected and hungry. When they are famished, they will become enraged; and looking upward, they will curse their king and their God."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          "Then they will look to the earth and see only distress and darkness and the gloom of anguish. And they will be driven into utter darkness."
        ]
      }
    ],
